#!/usr/bin/env ssc
---
name: enum-shared-casename
---

# two enums sharing a parameterless case name

Regression for the JS backend. Two enums that share a parameterless case name
(`ObligationStatus.Pending` and `DeferredActionStatus.Pending`) each hoisted a
global `const Pending = …`, so the emitted bundle had a duplicate `const`
declaration and Node rejected it with `Identifier 'Pending' has already been
declared`. The second declaration is now skipped (tags are global-by-name, so
the case objects are structurally identical); each enum's companion still
resolves its own `.Pending`.

```scalascript
enum ObligationStatus:
  case Pending
  case Active

enum DeferredActionStatus:
  case Pending
  case Done

val o1 = ObligationStatus.Pending
val d1 = DeferredActionStatus.Pending

println(o1 == ObligationStatus.Pending)
println(o1 == ObligationStatus.Active)
println(d1 == DeferredActionStatus.Pending)
println(d1 == DeferredActionStatus.Done)
println(ObligationStatus.values.size)
println(DeferredActionStatus.values.size)
```
